  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nPutting a `@NotNull` or `@NotEmpty` annotation on a method parameter should end up in openapi.json as marking the parameter required\r\n\r\n```\r\n    @POST\r\n    public void addFoo(@NotEmpty @NotNull String foo) {\r\n        ;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nresults in \r\n\r\n```\r\n      \"post\" : {\r\n        \"tags\" : [ \"Main\" ],\r\n        \"requestBody\" : {\r\n          \"content\" : {\r\n            \"application/json\" : {\r\n              \"schema\" : {\r\n                \"type\" : \"string\"\r\n              }\r\n            }\r\n          }\r\n        },\r\n        \"responses\" : {\r\n          \"201\" : {\r\n            \"description\" : \"Created\"\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nEven with those two annotations present an explicit `@RequestBody(required = true)` is needed\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMark the method parameter as required once one of the 2 bean-validation annotations are present\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n_No response_\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n_No response_\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
